      "name": "LockBit Ransomware Gang Targets NHS Trusts Across England",
      "description": "The National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) has issued an advisory today warning NHS trusts of an active LockBit ransomware campaign targeting healthcare organisations across England. Intelligence indicates that the LockBit group has been actively exploiting CVE-2024-3094, a critical remote code execution vulnerability in widely-deployed server software. At least three NHS trusts have confirmed incidents. The attacks follow a pattern of phishing emails delivering a loader, followed by credential dumping and lateral movement before deploying the ransomware payload. Organisations are strongly urged to apply the relevant patches immediately, review backup procedures, enable multi-factor authentication, and monitor for indicators of compromise. The NCSC has published a set of IOCs on its advisory page.",
